006.","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephan","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , preserving the vowels of the Greek name."]},{"name":"Steven","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , reflecting the normal pronunciation of the name in the English-speaking world."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":0,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Stephen Kendall was born in 1382, in Duloe, Cornwall, England as the son of John KENDALL. He married Mrs Christine Kendall in 1400, in Duloe, Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after 1450."},"et":{"1382–after 1450":"1382–pärast 1450","1382–1450":"1382–1450","1384–Female":"1384–Surnud","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1356–1403":"1356–1403","before March 1403":"enne märtsi 1403","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1410":"1410","1384":"1384","1450":"1450","after 1450":"pärast 1450","1382":"1382","1470":"1470","9 December 1449":"9. detsember 1449","Duloe, Cornwall, England":"Duloe, Cornwall, England","1678717, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1382–after 1450":"1382–1450 jälkeen","1382–1450":"1382–1450","1384–Female":"1384–Kuollut","1410–1470":"1410–1470","1356–1403":"1356–1403","before March 1403":"ennen vuotta maaliskuu 1403","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1410":"1410","1384":"1384","1450":"1450","after 1450":"1